SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FROM TIME TO TIME, THE LEAGUE MUST ASSESS THE NEED TO ACCRUE OR DISCLOSE A POSSIBLE LOSS CONTINGENCY FOR PROPOSED ADJUSTMENTS FROM VARIOUS FEDERAL AND STATE TAX AUTHORITIES WHO MAY AUDIT THE LEAGUE IN THE NORMAL COURSE OF BUSINESS. IT IS THE LEAGUE'S POLICY TO RECOGNIZE INTEREST AND/OR PENALITIES RELATED TO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS, AS INCOME TAX EXPENSE. THE LEAGUE HAS EVALUATED ITS TAX REPORTING AND HAS NOT REFLECTED ANY CONTINGENT LIABILITY FOR ANY SUCH PONTENTIAL ASSESSMENT.
